    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-13T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-13T09:00:00-05:00" n="445"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d445">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9332: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-13T22:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 13, 1937—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 13—10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>474. Artillery firing northeastern area between Japanese and Chinese since 4
                    o’clock this afternoon. At 8 o’clock tonight extending to general area civic
                    center. Japanese Vice Consul informally requested member of my staff to inform
                    appropriate American nationals and I have done so that Japanese Navy had decided
                    to use anti-aircraft guns against Chinese planes and that commercial planes
                    would fly over Japanese naval vessels at their own risk.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Department. Repeated to Nanking, Peiping, Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
